n: The case concerns whether the Helms-Burton Act\'s provisions apply to Cuban government entities, allowing U.S. companies like Exxon Mobil to pursue claims against them in U.S. courts.\n  - id: 24-758, name: GEO Group, Inc. v. Menocal, description: The case is about whether a private contractor working for the government can be immune from a lawsuit when they follow instructions, similar to how government employees are protected.\n  - id: 24-1234, name: United States v. Hemani, description: The case of United States v. Hemani, docket number 24-1234, concerns whether the government can temporarily disarm habitual marijuana users who continue to use the substance frequently. The issue revolves around a law that restricts Second Amendment rights for individuals who pose a perceived public safety risk due to their drug use.\n  - id: 22-58, name: United States v. Texas, description: The case centers on a dispute over the US government\'s immigration enforcement priorities, with the issue being whether states have standing to challenge federal policies and whether the government must apprehend and remove all non-citizens as required by law.\n  - id: 24-813, name: Chevron USA Inc. v. Plaquemines Parish, description: Chevron USA Inc. is disputing a local parish\'s authority to regulate its activities, arguing that it should be allowed to remove the case to federal court due to its connection with the federal government\'s wartime efforts.\n  - id: 23-1141, name: Smith & Wesson Brands v. Estados Unidos Mexicanos, description: The case Smith & Wesson Brands v. Estados Unidos Mexicanos concerns Mexico\'s claim that American firearms companies are responsible for cartel violence in Mexico, with the government seeking to hold these companies liable for the harm caused by smuggled guns.\n  - id: 25-95, name: Pung v. Isabella County, description: The case Pung v. Isabella County concerns whether the government must pay fair market value for a home taken due to unpaid taxes, rather than its lower auction price.\n\nFollow these rules:\n- Extract parameters strictly according to the schema.\n- Apply the extraction instructions above.\n- Use context only when the user refers indirectly (e.g., "it", "that one").\n- If a parameter cannot be extracted, set it to null.\n- Return ONLY valid JSON. No commentary.\n\nReturn JSON in this format:\n{\n    "parameters": {\n        <param_name>: <value or null>\n    },\n    "reasoning": "<brief explanation>"\n}\n',)
